    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-04-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-04-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="349"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d349">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Sir <persName
                            type="to">Julian Pauncefote</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-04-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 24, 1895</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 86.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge receipt of
                    your note of the 20th ultimo, in which you state that Her Majesty’s Government
                    agrees to pay one-third of the expense of the surveys of the Samoan land
                    commission, aggregating, perhaps, $2,000, provided the Government of the United
                    States concurs.</p>
                <p>In reply, I have to inform you that this Government will assume one-third of that
                    expense, and that the German ambassador here has been so advised in reply to his
                    note upon the subject.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q. Gresham.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
